Team Isengards goals for this project are to simplify the creation and hosting of UCI club websites through Campus Organizations so that the club web hosting is accessible to students with a variety of technical skills.
Providing high quality web hosting that uses popular open source software means that UCI club websites will always be secure and free of charge for students.

As board members in two campus clubs, Team Isengard hopes to ensure that free and secure web hosting is always available through UCI Campus Organizations and that these websites are easy maintain by current and future officers in UCI clubs.
Providing high quality web hosting that uses popular open source software means that UCI club websites will always be secure and free of charge for students.
The estimated budget for this project is $3000.  It is expected to be a relatively short and simple project that will be carried out by the members of team Isengard and a few hired workers.

The implementation of Wordpress into UCI's existing web hosting service is a huge step forward in promoting various campus organization's online presence.  Some club officers have little to no experience in web development, so some organizations don't even have a website or the one they have is poorly built.

Since the project is being run by team Isengard and possibly a few hired workers, we are going to need as much help implementing the system as possible.  In order to develop a successful system we require the input and support of our clients - most importantly the club officers who will be using it.

A risk with this project is the lack of interest in the new system.  Even though it will make the creation of websites easier, some organizations may simply not want to create a website or use the Wordpress system.  This leads to wasted time and money for carrying out the project.  Another risk is that the features of the system may not be fleshed out.  For example, it may be so easy to create a webpage that the designer goes overboard with plug-ins, modules, and such.

An online guide written for the school specifically about the deployment and maintenance of WordPress on its servers:
This would include a step by step tutorial of how to get a good looking demo site up and running.
A section on general trouble shooting and links to online resources.
A section on site look and feel guidelines.
A section on how to restore the site from a backup and how to reset to the default install.
Users should have access to the WordPress administrator login page through the clubs.uci.edu homepage.
